  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nThe Lighthouse book notes:\r\n\r\n> Note: due to the Docker Hub image being compiled to work on arbitrary machines, it isn't as highly optimized as an image built from source. We're working to improve this, but for now if you want the absolute best performance, please build the image yourself.\r\n\r\nI think we should add jobs to our CI workflow that build the Docker images with `--features modern`, which may also require adding a new build arg here:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/fff01b24ddedcd54486e374460855ca20d3dd232/Dockerfile#L4\r\n\r\nAnd a branch in the Makefile here:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/fff01b24ddedcd54486e374460855ca20d3dd232/Makefile#L24-L29\r\n\r\nFinally, CI glue to build and publish the modern image:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/fff01b24ddedcd54486e374460855ca20d3dd232/.github/workflows/docker.yml#L75-L78\r\n\r\nI think the naming scheme should add `-modern`, i.e. `latest-modern`, `latest-unstable-modern`, `v2.1.0-modern`",
